WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:03.503
(wind blowing)

00:03.545 --> 00:05.547
(birds singing)

00:05.588 --> 00:07.674
(engine revving)

00:11.094 --> 00:13.680
♪ ♪

00:18.518 --> 00:21.146
You don't have
to do this.

00:22.856 --> 00:25.025
You can just say
you didn't find me. Please.

00:25.066 --> 00:27.777
Please just call whoever...
(crying)

00:27.819 --> 00:30.196
Please just say
you didn't find me.

00:39.622 --> 00:41.583
Call speed dial two.

00:41.624 --> 00:42.584
WOMAN (over P.A.):
Attention, passengers...

00:42.625 --> 00:44.252
(beeping)

00:44.294 --> 00:45.754
Redial.

00:47.130 --> 00:48.214
(beeping)

00:48.256 --> 00:49.340
Call s... Is someone there?

00:49.382 --> 00:51.217
I need help. I need help.

00:51.259 --> 00:53.553
WOMAN:
What's up? Hey.
I'm sorry, my, uh...

00:53.595 --> 00:55.722
I don't know what's wrong
with my phone.

00:55.764 --> 00:58.224
Something's wrong.
It's not letting me dial out.
Here. Let me see.

00:59.142 --> 01:00.268
Uh...

01:00.310 --> 01:01.811
Oh, you're out
of cell range.

01:01.853 --> 01:03.438
Where'd you
get here from?
Uh, Minnesota.

01:03.480 --> 01:04.939
Yeah, it must not work
internationally.

01:04.981 --> 01:06.149
Sorry, I got to go.
Okay, could you...

01:06.191 --> 01:07.817
Oh, it's kind of an emergency.

01:07.859 --> 01:09.569
My friend is supposed
to meet me here, and she...

01:09.611 --> 01:11.613
I don't... she's not, like,
she's over two hours late,

01:11.654 --> 01:13.698
so I don't know where she is.
Oh. Okay...

01:13.740 --> 01:15.366
So, could you try
from your phone?

01:15.408 --> 01:17.577
If you put, uh, the speed dial
two into your phone,

01:17.619 --> 01:19.120
and then if you'd try it?

01:19.162 --> 01:20.538
Sure, sure,
yeah, of course.

01:20.580 --> 01:21.915
Um...

01:21.956 --> 01:24.459
"Jennifer Walker"?
Yeah.

01:25.376 --> 01:26.920
Okay.

01:26.961 --> 01:30.465
(rings, beeping)
Oh. It's not going through.

01:30.507 --> 01:32.467
Listen, I'm so sorry,
but I've really got to go.

01:32.509 --> 01:35.970
I got to catch
my bus. Here.
Okay. Um...

01:36.012 --> 01:37.514
Well...

01:37.555 --> 01:40.391
I'm really sorry
I couldn't help more.

01:47.774 --> 01:50.151
(breath trembling):
Oh...

01:50.193 --> 01:52.278
(exhales, sniffles)

01:53.446 --> 01:55.323
(whispers):
Oh, God.

01:59.869 --> 02:01.955
♪ ♪

02:07.877 --> 02:10.088
Call Gordon Howard
speed dial one.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.464
(toilet flushing nearby)

02:11.506 --> 02:12.882
(beeping)

02:12.924 --> 02:15.343
Call Jennifer Walker,
speed dial two.

02:18.012 --> 02:20.265
(beeping)
(frustrated grunt)

02:23.101 --> 02:24.769
(exhales)

02:27.063 --> 02:29.107
(door creaks open)

02:32.569 --> 02:34.654
(indistinct chatter,
P.A. announcements)

02:36.781 --> 02:38.908
(muffled music playing)

02:40.076 --> 02:43.037
Excuse me?
(clears throat)

02:43.079 --> 02:45.498
Yeah?
Is there somewhere
I could check

02:45.540 --> 02:48.334
if a bus is running late or
didn't arrive or something?

02:48.376 --> 02:50.461
I don't know.

02:50.503 --> 02:53.464
Uh, I'd probably try
the ticket booth.

02:53.506 --> 02:55.133
Okay, and where is that?

02:55.175 --> 02:57.343
Just, that's
just the way you're going,

02:57.385 --> 02:59.345
just all the way down.

02:59.387 --> 03:00.513
Okay.

03:00.555 --> 03:02.265
Forward.

03:02.307 --> 03:04.350
MAN:
Yeah, it came in
about an hour ago.

03:04.392 --> 03:06.186
My friend was on that
bus, and I can't...

03:06.227 --> 03:07.478
I can't find her.

03:07.520 --> 03:08.855
Could you...
Maybe you can help.

03:08.897 --> 03:10.148
Sure.
Could you help me?

03:10.190 --> 03:12.525
Yeah. Uh, what
does she look like?

03:12.567 --> 03:13.985
Um...

03:14.027 --> 03:16.196
she's shorter than me,

03:16.237 --> 03:18.072
uh, and she's, uh...

03:18.114 --> 03:20.366
she has...

03:20.408 --> 03:21.743
um...

03:22.869 --> 03:24.829
She has brown hair...

03:24.871 --> 03:30.168
and she has, uh, she has...

03:30.210 --> 03:32.670
she has brown eyes.

03:32.712 --> 03:34.088
Um...

03:37.050 --> 03:39.260
My age.

03:39.302 --> 03:41.429
(laughs softly)

03:41.471 --> 03:43.139
Uh, that's...

03:43.181 --> 03:45.225
that's all I got.

03:46.851 --> 03:49.938
MAN:
I'll let you know if I see her.

03:49.979 --> 03:51.314
MURPHY:
Thanks.

03:51.356 --> 03:53.441
♪ ♪

03:54.484 --> 03:56.486
Call speed dial two.

03:57.862 --> 03:59.489
(beeping)

03:59.530 --> 04:01.616
♪ ♪

04:06.454 --> 04:08.706
MAN (over P.A.):
Bus 319 now arriving

04:08.748 --> 04:11.376
at Platform Three
from Thunder Bay.

04:11.417 --> 04:13.419
(phone keys tapping)

04:13.461 --> 04:15.213
(text sends)

04:16.965 --> 04:20.635
Hey. When's the next
bus to Thunder Bay?

04:24.055 --> 04:26.808
MAN:
Looks like 7:15 a.m.

04:26.849 --> 04:28.601
Tomorrow?

04:28.643 --> 04:30.311
Yeah.

04:30.353 --> 04:32.605
(phone keys tapping)

04:32.647 --> 04:34.816
Sorry, I'm not
really, uh...

04:34.857 --> 04:36.401
(tapping stops)

04:36.442 --> 04:38.361
...I'm not really
familiar with the area,

04:38.403 --> 04:41.197
but my, uh, friend is
flying out of there...

04:41.239 --> 04:44.075
(sniffs) ...at 4:00 tomorrow,
and I need to get to him

04:44.117 --> 04:46.494
before... he leaves.

04:46.536 --> 04:49.497
Would I make it
if I took the...

04:49.539 --> 04:51.791
took that bus?

04:51.833 --> 04:55.461
I mean, it's, like,
a five-hour drive, so...

04:55.503 --> 04:57.672
yeah, you should.

04:57.714 --> 04:59.090
Yeah?

04:59.132 --> 05:00.800
Yeah.

05:03.511 --> 05:05.096
Okay.

05:07.682 --> 05:10.852
The ticket booth is...
is, uh, this way, right?

05:10.893 --> 05:12.979
Down this way?
Yeah, uh, just straight ahead.

05:13.021 --> 05:15.273
To the left?
Yeah.

05:16.232 --> 05:18.318
♪ ♪

05:25.950 --> 05:28.119
MAN (over P.A.):
Now approaching the platform,

05:28.161 --> 05:31.039
Eastbound 164 to Thunder Bay.

05:33.082 --> 05:34.751
(groans)

05:37.420 --> 05:39.714
All right, buddy. Go.

05:42.425 --> 05:45.053
(quietly):
Come on, Pretzel. Come on, boy.

05:51.976 --> 05:54.020
DRIVER (over speaker):
Good morning.

05:54.062 --> 05:56.856
First stop Fort Frances,
last stop Thunder Bay.

05:56.898 --> 05:58.649
Based on current traffic,

05:58.691 --> 06:01.944
our ETA looks to be
about 5:30 p.m.

06:04.572 --> 06:07.241
5:30? What the...

06:07.283 --> 06:09.369
Excuse me?

06:09.410 --> 06:11.287
Excuse me?
Uh, ma'am,

06:11.329 --> 06:12.914
you need to
take your seat.

06:12.955 --> 06:14.999
I thought this was
only a five-hour drive.

06:15.041 --> 06:16.667
Yes, but we've got
about ten stops.

06:16.709 --> 06:18.378
So please,
take your seat.
Wait, I'm sorry,

06:18.419 --> 06:20.296
I-I have to be there by 4:00.

06:20.338 --> 06:22.507
Excuse me?
Is there an express bus, or...

06:22.548 --> 06:24.384
No. Ma'am,

06:24.425 --> 06:26.594
please take your seat.
I can't stop...
I need to get off.

06:26.636 --> 06:28.221
till Fort Frances, ma'am.
No, please, I really need
to get off, please.

06:28.262 --> 06:30.515
Please, I need to get off.

06:30.556 --> 06:32.683
Okay, okay. All right,
calm down, calm down.

06:32.725 --> 06:34.685
I'm pulling over.

06:37.939 --> 06:40.024
♪ ♪

06:46.989 --> 06:48.866
(exhales)

07:01.254 --> 07:02.463
Open to Uber.
(beep)

07:02.505 --> 07:03.923
(beeping)

07:03.965 --> 07:05.007
(sighs)

07:05.049 --> 07:07.510
I need help!

07:07.552 --> 07:10.388
Could somebody help me, please?

07:12.223 --> 07:14.350
Please? Anyone? I need help!

07:16.644 --> 07:17.979
Someone, I...
Hi.

07:18.020 --> 07:19.564
Are-are you okay?
No, I'm not.

07:19.605 --> 07:21.524
Um, could I please
use your phone

07:21.566 --> 07:22.984
to order an Uber, 'cause
mine's-mine's not working.

07:23.025 --> 07:24.652
Yeah. Yeah, sure.
I'm stuck.

07:24.694 --> 07:26.028
I think that
would be okay.
Yeah, I'll p...

07:26.070 --> 07:27.655
I'll pay you for it.
Where you going?

07:27.697 --> 07:29.323
I'm going
to Thunder Bay Airport.

07:29.365 --> 07:31.284
Thunder Bay?
Yeah.

07:31.325 --> 07:33.453
I don't think you're gonna get
someone to take you that far.

07:33.494 --> 07:34.662
Well, I have...
I have money.

07:34.704 --> 07:36.122
I have, like,
300 bucks in here.

07:36.164 --> 07:37.915
More. I have a little more
than 300 bucks.

07:37.957 --> 07:39.667
I'm so sorry, but
even if one agreed

07:39.709 --> 07:42.044
to take you, it would be a
lot more than what you have,

07:42.086 --> 07:44.338
and I just can't...

07:44.380 --> 07:46.632
Is there anyone
else I can call...
No, there's nobody else you c...

07:46.674 --> 07:48.342
There's nobody else.

07:50.303 --> 07:52.597
Okay.

07:52.638 --> 07:54.390
Good luck.

07:54.432 --> 07:57.518
(taking deep breaths)

07:59.937 --> 08:02.398
(exhales)

08:02.440 --> 08:04.525
(Pretzel whines anxiously)

08:04.567 --> 08:06.903
Aw, buddy, I'm sorry.

08:06.944 --> 08:09.906
I'll get you something,
all right? Come on.

08:09.947 --> 08:13.409
Find inside. Okay, okay.

08:13.451 --> 08:15.661
(pop song plays softly)

08:25.630 --> 08:27.131
(whines softly)

08:27.173 --> 08:29.008
(whispers):
Here you go, buddy.

08:36.974 --> 08:40.311
MAN:
Um, there's, uh,
someone that's sitting here.

08:42.230 --> 08:43.898
Sorry.

08:46.609 --> 08:47.777
Uh...
(clears throat)

08:47.818 --> 08:49.654
...do you want me to move?

08:49.695 --> 08:51.531
No, you don't have to.

08:51.572 --> 08:53.699
'Cause I don't care.

08:54.659 --> 08:57.912
Okay. I'm just gonna
keep studying, then.

08:59.997 --> 09:03.084
(whispering): 15, 13,
then if I carry 18...

09:03.125 --> 09:04.919
(continues inaudibly)

09:05.878 --> 09:08.589
Will you drive me
to Thunder Bay for 300 bucks?

09:08.631 --> 09:10.967
I'm trying to get
to my grandma's funeral.

09:13.511 --> 09:17.890
Um, no, sorry, I-I can't.
I have school.

09:17.932 --> 09:20.393
How old are you?

09:20.434 --> 09:22.144
Uh, 16.

09:23.771 --> 09:25.731
You like sitting in coffee shops

09:25.773 --> 09:28.192
before school?
I don't mean to be rude,
it's just, um,

09:28.234 --> 09:31.571
I'm really not prepared
for this test today, so...

09:31.612 --> 09:34.782
if you'll excuse me,
I'm just gonna keep studying.

09:34.824 --> 09:37.118
(whispering):
Oliver has
a pair of shoes...

09:37.159 --> 09:39.662
(continues indistinctly)

09:39.704 --> 09:43.332
You know what I used to do
when I wasn't ready for a test?

09:43.374 --> 09:44.834
What?

09:44.875 --> 09:46.252
(sighs)

09:46.294 --> 09:48.129
Not go.

09:48.170 --> 09:50.339
Sorry, that-that's not
an option for me.

09:52.008 --> 09:53.634
Why?

09:53.676 --> 09:55.344
Because...

09:55.386 --> 09:57.847
Because why, it's
against the rules?

09:57.888 --> 10:00.558
Yeah.
Are you seriously

10:00.600 --> 10:03.227
gonna tell me that a single day
of school is more important

10:03.269 --> 10:06.147
than me being able to bury
my beloved grandmother?

10:09.525 --> 10:11.819
Well, I-I'm-I'm not allowed
to drive my dad's car,

10:11.861 --> 10:14.113
so I couldn't take you
even if I wanted to.

10:14.155 --> 10:16.907
Oh, what's your name?
What's your name?

10:16.949 --> 10:18.868
Michael.

10:18.909 --> 10:22.288
Hi, Michael. I'm,
uh... I'm Lorri.

10:22.330 --> 10:27.710
Okay? Um...
I missed my bus.

10:27.752 --> 10:30.171
And I don't know how else
to get to the funeral.

10:30.212 --> 10:33.215
'Cause no one will drive me,
but I can't drive myself,

10:33.257 --> 10:35.801
'cause I'm sure
you can tell I'm blind.

10:36.761 --> 10:40.473
You know, my grandma and I--
we were super close.

10:40.514 --> 10:42.933
We were really close, Michael.

10:42.975 --> 10:45.770
And if I don't go to this,
I, um...

10:47.897 --> 10:49.690
I just... I...

10:49.732 --> 10:52.026
I can't, so, please.

10:52.068 --> 10:55.905
I... I-I just...
I can't. Okay?

10:55.946 --> 10:57.740
If-if I don't go to school,
they're gonna call my mom.

10:57.782 --> 10:59.909
I can call. I can call.

10:59.950 --> 11:01.744
I'll call. I'll call...
Um, I can say...

11:01.786 --> 11:03.204
I'll pretend to be your mom
and say you're sick.

11:03.245 --> 11:04.455
You know what?
She's not gonna know.

11:04.497 --> 11:06.540
Okay, well-well, what about

11:06.582 --> 11:07.917
when she comes home
and I'm not there?

11:07.958 --> 11:09.251
What time does
she come home?

11:09.293 --> 11:11.128
La-- Not until, like, late.

11:11.170 --> 11:13.255
Like, 2:00 maybe?
2:00 a.m.?!

11:13.297 --> 11:15.549
Yeah, she-she's a nurse, and
she works the graveyard shift.

11:15.591 --> 11:17.051
Oh, you're gonna be home
way before then.

11:17.093 --> 11:19.637
Wait. Is your dad home?
Where's your dad?

11:20.638 --> 11:22.682
He's-he's ice fishing
with my uncle.

11:22.723 --> 11:24.892
He's ice fishing? He's not home.

11:24.934 --> 11:26.936
Look, I mean...
(laughing):
He's not home.

11:26.977 --> 11:29.563
Shh. I'm not stealing
my dad's car.

11:29.605 --> 11:31.691
Michael, you're gonna borrow
your dad's car.

11:31.732 --> 11:33.234
You're gonna
borrow his car.

11:33.275 --> 11:35.111
You'll be there and
back with time to spare.

11:35.152 --> 11:39.031
And your other option
is failing that test.

11:40.991 --> 11:43.077
Michael, listen to me.

11:44.328 --> 11:47.039
I used to be like you
when I was a kid.

11:47.081 --> 11:49.750
I was so worried about my
parents getting mad at me

11:49.792 --> 11:51.711
for literally everything.

11:51.752 --> 11:54.797
And then, I went blind,

11:54.839 --> 11:58.384
and I was like,
"What is the point?"

12:00.302 --> 12:02.388
Yeah, but I-I'm not blind,

12:02.430 --> 12:04.557
so that argument
doesn't really apply here.

12:04.598 --> 12:08.519
My point is, it was a relief
to let go of the pressure.

12:08.561 --> 12:10.104
And I want you to do that.

12:10.146 --> 12:12.189
I want you to do

12:12.231 --> 12:15.359
what you want to do for once.

12:17.153 --> 12:22.450
♪ I hate it when you go,
I hate it when you go... ♪

12:22.491 --> 12:26.620
So... so that... that actually
worked out for you?

12:26.662 --> 12:29.123
♪ I hate it when you go,
I hate it when you go... ♪

12:29.165 --> 12:30.666
Yeah.

12:30.708 --> 12:33.753
Yeah, it did. It did.

12:33.794 --> 12:35.880
♪ ♪

12:43.137 --> 12:45.222
(engine revs)

12:47.558 --> 12:49.643
Okay. That felt
really good.

12:50.561 --> 12:52.646
Told you.

12:53.898 --> 12:55.983
(engine revving)

13:04.158 --> 13:06.243
♪ ♪

13:28.599 --> 13:30.601
Why are you driving,
like, two miles an hour?

13:30.643 --> 13:33.604
I'm going ten kilometers
under the speed limit,

13:33.646 --> 13:35.439
'cause that's what they told me
to do in drivers ed.

13:35.481 --> 13:37.107
Of course.

13:37.149 --> 13:39.026
Relax. Uh...
(laughs)

13:39.068 --> 13:41.403
I said that we'd be
there by, like...

13:41.445 --> 13:43.113
on time.

13:43.155 --> 13:45.699
Okay. (sniffles)

13:45.741 --> 13:47.993
You know, you can
sleep if you want.

13:48.035 --> 13:50.037
No, it's fine.
I just want to get there.

13:51.580 --> 13:53.958
Keep me awake.
What was your test on?

13:53.999 --> 13:56.752
Just, like,
French-Canadian militiamen

13:56.794 --> 13:59.296
and the First Nations
defending Canada during 1812.

13:59.338 --> 14:00.965
Nothing...
Oh, my God.

14:01.006 --> 14:03.175
No. I'm tireder.

14:03.217 --> 14:06.762
Yeah, uh, to be honest,
I probably would have failed it.

14:07.721 --> 14:09.682
You're also probably
one of those people

14:09.723 --> 14:11.308
who thinks a "B" is an "F."

14:12.268 --> 14:15.813
Well, uh, not really me,
but my mom certainly is.

14:15.855 --> 14:18.524
(laughs)
She's just really, um...

14:18.566 --> 14:21.026
She-She's withholding,
basically.
Mm.

14:21.068 --> 14:22.778
I don't... I don't really
know how to explain it.

14:22.820 --> 14:24.780
She's, um...

14:24.822 --> 14:26.824
A bitch?

14:26.866 --> 14:28.325
(snorts)

14:28.367 --> 14:30.369
Yeah. (laughs)

14:30.411 --> 14:31.745
That-that-that sums it up
pretty nicely.

14:31.787 --> 14:33.622
She's-she... she's a bitch.

14:33.664 --> 14:35.791
So, um,

14:35.833 --> 14:38.168
can I ask you something?

14:38.210 --> 14:40.254
Here it comes.

14:40.296 --> 14:42.047
Here-here what comes?

14:42.089 --> 14:44.091
Was I born blind?
Are my other senses heightened?

14:44.133 --> 14:46.302
What do I think
you look like?

14:46.343 --> 14:48.304
Yeah. (laughs)
Yeah?

14:48.345 --> 14:50.431
Yeah, uh, all-all of those.
Okay.

14:50.472 --> 14:53.142
I... No, I lost my sight
when I was 14.

14:53.183 --> 14:55.102
No, they are not.

14:55.144 --> 15:00.065
And I've realized I don't know
what anyone looks like, so...

15:00.107 --> 15:01.817
That's crazy. So-so,
you're telling me that you have,

15:01.859 --> 15:04.486
like, no idea how hot you are?

15:08.073 --> 15:10.075
(sighs)
You know, you're, like, a kid.

15:10.117 --> 15:11.493
I'm not gonna hook up with you.

15:11.535 --> 15:13.203
Oh, no. Sorry.
That's-that...

15:13.245 --> 15:15.039
That's-that's not
what I meant. Sorry.

15:15.080 --> 15:16.957
Doesn't matter how old you are.
I don't care if you're young.

15:16.999 --> 15:18.459
No, seriously, seriously.
It doesn't give you the right...

15:18.500 --> 15:20.127
Lorri, listen to me.
Um, that's-that's not me.

15:20.169 --> 15:21.921
I don't say that...
I mean, I'm in the car
with you

15:21.962 --> 15:22.838
by myself
in the middle of nowhere.
Like, Lorri, I'm...

15:22.880 --> 15:25.424
It's not cool.
I'm gay.

15:25.466 --> 15:27.009
Oh.

15:29.720 --> 15:32.139
Well, regardless
if you're gay or straight,

15:32.181 --> 15:33.849
you shouldn't say things

15:33.891 --> 15:36.226
like that to women.
It's gross.

15:36.268 --> 15:40.230
Sorry. Um, I'm-I'm just used
to, uh,

15:40.272 --> 15:42.483
like, saying whatever I think
a straight guy would say,

15:42.524 --> 15:44.610
so people don't
suspect anything.

15:44.652 --> 15:46.695
Oh, so you're not out?

15:46.737 --> 15:49.949
No, um, only to you, now,

15:49.990 --> 15:52.660
and, uh, certain corners
of the Internet.

15:52.701 --> 15:56.038
So, wait. Have you not...?
You never hooked up with a dude?

15:56.080 --> 15:57.539
No.

15:57.581 --> 16:00.626
Well, I mean,
it's gonna happen one day.

16:00.668 --> 16:03.796
Yeah, or, um...

16:03.837 --> 16:06.590
tonight, maybe.

16:06.632 --> 16:09.051
What do you mean, tonight?

16:09.093 --> 16:11.595
